  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What do I eat on the Ketogenics Diet?",
  "response": "The ketogenic diet, commonly known as the keto diet, is a high-fat, low-carbohydrate eating plan designed to put your body into a state of ketosis, where it burns fat for energy instead of carbohydrates. Here\u2019s a breakdown of foods you can eat on the ketogenic diet:\n\n### Foods to Eat:\n\n**1. Healthy Fats:**\n   - Avocado oil\n   - Olive oil\n   - Coconut oil\n   - Butter and ghee\n   - Lard\n   - Fatty fish (salmon, sardines)\n   - Nuts and seeds (almonds, walnuts, chia seeds, flaxseeds)\n   - Nut butters (almond butter, peanut butter without added sugars)\n\n**2. Protein Sources:**\n   - Eggs\n   - Grass-fed meat (beef, lamb, pork)\n   - Poultry (chicken, turkey)\n   - Fatty fish (tuna, mackerel)\n   - Shellfish (shrimp, crabs)\n   - Low-carb protein powders (whey, pea protein)\n\n**3. Low-Carbohydrate Vegetables:**\n   - Leafy greens (spinach, kale, arugula)\n   - Cruciferous vegetables (broccoli, cauliflower, Brussels sprouts)\n   - Zucchini\n   - Bell peppers\n   - Asparagus\n   - Mushrooms\n   - Cabbage\n   - Green beans\n\n**4. Dairy Products (if tolerated):**\n   - Cheese (cheddar, mozzarella, goat cheese)\n   - Heavy cream\n   - Greek yogurt (unsweetened, full-fat)\n   - Sour cream (full-fat, avoid added sugars)\n\n**5. Berries (in moderation):**\n   - Raspberries\n   - Strawberries\n   - Blackberries\n\n### Foods to Avoid:\n\n**1. High-Carbohydrate Foods:**\n   - Grains (bread, rice, pasta, cereals)\n   - Sugary foods (candies, desserts, sweetened beverages)\n   - High-carb fruits (bananas, apples, grapes)\n\n**2. Starchy Vegetables:**\n   - Potatoes\n   - Corn\n   - Peas\n\n**3. Processed Foods:**\n   - Any foods with added sugars or high-fructose corn syrup\n   - Most snack foods (chips, crackers)\n\n**4. Legumes:**\n   - Beans\n   - Lentils\n   - Chickpeas\n\n### Tips for Success:\n- **Stay Hydrated:** Drink plenty of water, and consider electrolytes, as a keto diet can lead to fluid loss.\n- **Meal Prep:** Planning meals in advance can help maintain adherence to the diet.\n- **Monitor Macronutrients:** Aim for a typical macronutrient ratio of approximately 70% fat, 25% protein, and 5% carbohydrates.\n\nBefore starting any diet, including the ketogenic diet, it's a good idea to consult with a healthcare provider or nutritionist, especially if you have any underlying health conditions.",
